# install.packages("xtable")
library(xtable)

cor_table <- function(x){ 
  require(Hmisc) 
  x <- as.matrix(x) 
  R <- rcorr(x)$r 
  p <- rcorr(x)$P 
  
  ## define notions for significance levels; spacing is important.
  mystars <- ifelse(p < .001, "***", ifelse(p < .01, "** ", ifelse(p < .05, "* ", " ")))
  
  ## trunctuate the matrix that holds the correlations to three decimal
  R <- format(round(cbind(rep(-1.11, ncol(x)), R), 3))[,-1] 
  
  ## build a new matrix that includes the correlations with their apropriate stars 
  Rnew <- matrix(paste(R, mystars, sep=""), ncol=ncol(x)) 
  diag(Rnew) <- paste(diag(R), " ", sep="") 
  rownames(Rnew) <- colnames(x) 
  colnames(Rnew) <- paste(colnames(x), "", sep="") 
  
  ## remove upper triangle
  Rnew <- as.matrix(Rnew)
  Rnew[upper.tri(Rnew, diag = TRUE)] <- ""
  Rnew <- as.data.frame(Rnew) 
  
  ## remove last column and return the matrix (which is now a data frame)
  Rnew <- cbind(Rnew[1:length(Rnew)-1])
  return(Rnew) 
}

  sd(x)/sqrt(length(x))
}

  1. Do t-test and show whether there is any significant difference in As concentration in rice (GAs) between low and high As soil treatments.
# Create two dataframes
T1 <- df.gh %>% dplyr::select(Treatment, GAs) %>%
         filter(Treatment == "High As")

T2 <- df.gh %>% dplyr::select(Treatment, GAs) %>%
         filter(Treatment == "Low As")

# Two-Sample T-test
t.test(x=T1$GAs,
       y=T2$GAs, 
       paired = TRUE,
       alternative = "greater")
## 
##  Paired t-test
## 
## data:  T1$GAs and T2$GAs
## t = 12.835, df = 20, p-value = 2.052e-11
## alternative hypothesis: true mean difference is greater than 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  0.754535      Inf
## sample estimates:
## mean difference 
##       0.8716667

p1<-ggbetweenstats(
  data = df.gh,
  x = Treatment,
  y = GAs,
  ylab = "GAs",
  type = "parametric", # ANOVA or Kruskal-Wallis
  var.equal = TRUE, # ANOVA or Welch ANOVA
  plot.type = "box",
  pairwise.comparisons = TRUE,
  pairwise.display = "significant",
  centrality.plotting = FALSE,
  bf.message = FALSE
)+
